acknowledgement(address,((string,bytes32.details: Verifies the given proof and calls the `onAcknowledgementPacket` function on the given `receiver` contract,    ie. the IBC dApp.    Prerequisite: the original packet is committed and not ack'ed or timed out yet.

params.ackPacket: The acknowledgement receipt for the packet
params.packet: The IbcPacket data for the acknowledged packet
params.proof: The membership proof to verify the packet acknowledgement committed on Polymer chain
params.receiver: The IbcReceiver contract that should handle the packet acknowledgement event If the address doesn't satisfy the interface, the transaction will be reverted.

closeIbcChannel(bytes32).details: Emits a `CloseIbcChannel` event with the given `channelId` and the address of the message sender

params.initClientMsg: The initial client state and consensus state.

params.channelId: IBC channel ID from the port perspective
params.portAddress: EVM address of the IBC port

returns._0: A channel struct is always returned. If it doesn't exists, the channel struct is populated with default    values per EVM.

incentivizedAcknowledgement(address,((st.details: Verifies the given proof and calls the `onAcknowledgementPacket` function on the given `receiver` contract,   ie. the IBC dApp.   Prerequisite: the original packet is committed and not ack'ed or timed out yet.

params.incentivizedAck: The incentivized acknowledgement from counterparty chain, where the relayer is the payee address on behalf of the forward relayer that delivered the packet
params.packet: The original IbcPacket data sent by the dApp
params.proof: The membership proof to verify the packet acknowledgement committed on Polymer chain
params.receiver: The dApp contract that should handle the app-level packet acknowledgement

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

recvPacket(address,((string,bytes32),(st.details: Verifies the given proof and calls the `onRecvPacket` function on the given `receiver` contractEmit an `RecvPacket` event with the details of the received packet; Also emit a WriteAckPacket event, which can be relayed to Polymer chain by relayers

params.packet: The IbcPacket data for the received packet
params.proof: The proof data needed to verify the packet receipt
params.receiver: The IbcReceiver contract that should handle the packet receipt event If the address doesn't satisfy the interface, the transaction will be reverted.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

sendPacket(bytes32,bytes,uint64,(uint256.details: Emits an `IbcPacketEvent` event containing the sender address, channel ID, packet data, and timeout block timestamp.

params.channelId: The ID of the channel on which to send the packet.
params.fee: The fee serves as the packet incentive for forward relay. It's escrowed on the running chain and will be    claimed by relayer later once the packet is delivered and ack'ed or timed out.    recvFee is always paid, but only ackFee or timeoutFee is paid, depending on packet path.    Total fee for packet roundtrip is determined by recvFee + max(ackFee, timeoutFee).
params.timeoutTimestamp: The timestamp in nanoseconds after which the packet times out if it has not been received.

timeout(address,((string,bytes32),(strin.details: Verifies the given proof and calls the `onTimeoutPacket` function on the given `receiver` contract, ie. the IBC-dApp. Prerequisite: the original packet is committed and not ack'ed or timed out yet.

params.packet: The IbcPacket data for the timed-out packet
params.proof: The non-membership proof data needed to verify the packet timeout
params.receiver: The IbcReceiver contract that should handle the packet timeout event If the address doesn't satisfy the interface, the transaction will be reverted.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgradeClient((bytes,(uint256,uint256,ui.details: Upgrades the Polymer client. It can only be run by CoreSC maintainer with a social consensus.

params.upgradeClientMsg: The new client state and consensus state.

closeIbcChannel(bytes32).notice: Close the specified IBC channel by channel ID Must be called by the channel owner, ie. portChannelMap[msg.sender][channelId] must exist

connectIbcChannel(address,bytes32,string.notice: This func is called by a 'relayer' after the IBC/VIBC hub chain has processed the onOpenIbcChannel event. The dApp should implement the onConnectIbcChannel method to handle the last two channel handshake methods, ie. ChanOpenAck or ChanOpenConfirm.

getChannel(address,bytes32).notice: Get the IBC channel with the specified port and channel ID

getTotalPacketFees(address,bytes32,uint6.notice: Return escrowed fees for a packet. Relayers can query this to determine if a packet is worth relaying.

incentivizedAcknowledgement(address,((st.notice: Handle the incentivized acknowledgement of an IBC packet by the counterparty

onCloseIbcChannel(address,bytes32,((uint.notice: This func is called by a 'relayer' after the IBC/VIBC hub chain has processed ChanCloseConfirm event. The dApp's onCloseIbcChannel callback is invoked. dApp should throw an error if the channel should not be closed.

openIbcChannel(address,string,uint8,bool.notice: This func is called by a 'relayer' on behalf of a dApp. The dApp should be implements IbcReceiver. The dApp should implement the onOpenIbcChannel method to handle one of the first two channel handshake methods, ie. ChanOpenInit or ChanOpenTry. If callback succeeds, the dApp should return the selected version, and an emitted event will be relayed to the IBC/VIBC hub chain.

payPacketFeeAsync(address,bytes32,uint64.notice: Pay extra fees for a packet that has already been sent. Dapps should call this function to incentivize packet relay if the packet is not ack'ed or timed out yet.This function can be called multiple times for the same packet. But it shouldn't be called if the channel is not incentivized.

recvPacket(address,((string,bytes32),(st.notice: Receive an IBC packet and then pass it to the IBC-dApp for processing if verification succeeds.

sendPacket(bytes32,bytes,uint64,(uint256.notice: Sends an IBC packet on a existing channel with the specified packet data and timeout block timestamp.Data should be encoded in a format defined by the channel version, and the module on the other side should know how to parse this.

writeTimeoutPacket(address,((string,byte.notice: Generate a timeout packet for the given packet
